04/07/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- NATO will adopt a timetable for the accession of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia sometime in 2006, Douglas Bereuter, the chief of the Alliance's Parliamentary Assembly said Friday (2 July). The three countries signed the so-called Adriatic Charter and are assisting each other on the path to membership.
In other news Friday, five countries of the Southeast European Co-operation Process -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro -- signed a memorandum of understanding on migration, asylum and refugee issues. The accord, signed in Tirana, will affect thousands of people in the region. (ATA, HINA - 03/07/04; AFP, Stability Pact press release, FENA - 02/07/04)
